<FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF" face="sans-serif">Hafta congratulate you guys on killing RF for your cleric friend today, musta been a proud moment!<BR><BR>I have never spoken publicly regarding events similar to what happened today, because, quite frankly, it's all part of the game, everyone gets burned at one time or another, but you simply went too far.  I have played this game longer than probably 90% of you guys and i have never seen anything like this.<BR><BR>I dunno if you guys do things like this simply because you can (I could honestly care less who was in the right according to GM rules concerning RF), or if it pleases you to be COMPLETELY disrespectful to others?  Clearly those of you who were there to kill RF do not have consciences or you would have done what was right.  However, now a cleric who did absolutely NOTHING to merit receiving his epic has it now.  <BR><BR>Maybe it's just a few of you who give an extremely bad name for your guild, but regardless, the actions of a few demonstrate the actions of the whole.  Sure, you've done some nice things for others, but the greater percentage of the things you guys do to/for others is bad and it's those acts that are remembered the most.  Those of you who DO have consciences i hope this weighs on you heavily, this was one of THE most disrespectful things i have ever witnessed in EQ.<BR><BR>Again, congratulations to your undeserving cleric friend.<BR><BR>Kavis Khaan<BR>Officer, Sanctus Arcanum<BR><BR><BR><BR></FONT><BR>
